.Dd January 28, 2026
.Dt PARADOS 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm parados
.Nd HTTP protocol for the parados media server
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
protocol describes the HTTP interface provided by
.Xr parados 1 .
It is intended for simple clients and scripts.
.Pp
The protocol uses HTTP/1.1.
Each request is handled on a separate connection, which is closed after
the response.
Persistent connections are not supported.
.Pp
Media items are identified by 64-bit identifiers encoded as 16 hexadecimal
digits.
.Sh REQUESTS
All endpoints accept
.Cm GET
and
.Cm HEAD
requests.
The server also accepts
.Cm OPTIONS
for CORS preflight.
.Sh AUTHENTICATION
If one or more users are configured,
HTTP Basic authentication is required for all endpoints except
.Pa /ping .
.Pp
Credentials are provided using the
.Cm Authorization
header.
.Pp
If no users are configured, authentication is disabled.
.Sh ENDPOINTS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa /ping
Health check endpoint.
Returns HTTP 200 with a short plain text body.
.It Pa /library
Return the media library as JSON.
Each entry contains an item identifier and a relative path.
.Pp
Response format:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
{ "proto": 1, "items": [ { "id": "...", "path": "..." } ] }
.Ed
.It Pa /meta/{id}
Return metadata for a single item.
The response includes the item identifier, path, size in bytes, and MIME
type.
.It Pa /stream/{id}
Stream the contents of a media item.
Supports byte range requests using the
.Cm Range
header.
.Pp
Valid ranges return HTTP 206.
Invalid ranges return HTTP 400 or HTTP 416.
.It Pa /queue
Return an M3U playlist containing stream URLs for all permitted items.
.Pp
If the request includes a
.Cm Host
header, it is used to construct playlist URLs.
.El
.Sh RESPONSES
The server sets
.Cm Content-Type
based on file extension.
Unknown types default to
.Cm application/octet-stream .
.Pp
Most responses include
.Cm Content-Length .
Streaming responses may omit it.
.Sh STATUS CODES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm 200
Request succeeded.
.It Cm 204
No content.
.It Cm 206
Partial content.
.It Cm 400
Bad request.
.It Cm 401
Authentication required or failed.
.It Cm 404
Resource not found or not permitted.
.It Cm 405
Method not allowed.
.It Cm 416
Requested range not satisfiable.
.It Cm 500
Internal server error.
.El
.Sh VERSIONING
JSON responses include a
.Cm proto
field indicating the protocol version.
Clients should reject unknown versions.
.Sh NOTES
The protocol does not provide sessions, persistent connections,
transcoding, or server-side state.
All higher-level behavior is handled by the client.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr parados 1 ,
.Xr parados.conf 5
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Abhinav Prasai

